Source: meshstor-nvme-rdma-dkms
Section: kernel
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Meshstor <support@example.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper (>= 13)
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://example.com/meshstor-ms

Package: meshstor-nvme-rdma-dkms
Architecture: all
Depends: dkms (>= 3.0), ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: linux-headers-generic
Description: nvme-rdma host driver with PCI P2PDMA support (DKMS backport)
 Rebuilds the running kernel's own nvme-rdma module with the upstream
 v7.1 commit 23528aa3320a ("nvme: enable PCI P2PDMA support for RDMA
 transport") backported, installed to updates/dkms where depmod prefers
 it over the in-tree module. In-tree nvme-core and nvme-fabrics are
 used unchanged; removing this package restores the stock module.
 .
 Supported kernel families: Ubuntu 24.04 HWE (6.17.*-generic),
 Ubuntu 26.04 (7.0.*-generic), RHEL/Rocky 10 (6.12.*.el10). Other
 kernels are skipped via BUILD_EXCLUSIVE_KERNEL and keep their stock
 driver.
